  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Slice your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the<strong> sliced potato</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 10-12 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1712068818337-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1712068818337-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1712068818337-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1712068818337-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1712068818337-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>dried yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[200ml] </span><strong>warm water </strong>and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p><p>While the yeast is developing, drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1712068823390-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1712068823390-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1712068823390-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1712068823390-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1712068823390-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the woody ends off your <strong>asparagus</strong>, then cut the <strong>trimmed</strong> <strong>asparagus</strong> in half, lengthways</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>pizza base mix </strong>to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[115ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>(you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1712068827256-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1712068827256-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1712068827256-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1712068827256-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1712068827256-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Tip the <strong>dough</strong> out onto a floured work surface and cut into 1 per person</p><p>Toss each <strong>dough ball </strong>in a light dusting of <strong>flour </strong>until coated, rounding the ball as you go (no need to knead!)</p><p>Press each <strong>dough ball</strong> in the centre and gently push outwards with your fingertips, leaving the rim of the pizza untouched to form a crust (don't worry if the dough rips, just stick it back together and carry on!)</p><p>Tip: Dust with extra sprinkles of flour as you go to stop it sticking!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1712068830852-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1712068830852-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1712068830852-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1712068830852-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1712068830852-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Keep going until your base is slightly bigger than a side plate – this is your<strong> pizza base</strong></p><p>Remove the tray[s] with the potato and onion from the oven and transfer the cooked veg to a clean board, discard the baking paper</p><p>Add the <strong>pizza base[s]</strong> to the tray[s] and top with the <strong>cooked potato</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
